    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR simplifies the `exec_place` hierarchy by removing unnecessary shell classes and introducing a cleaner RAII-based activation mechanism.\r\n\r\n### Key Changes\r\n\r\n- **Introduced `exec_place_scope`**: A movable RAII guard that manages execution context activation/deactivation. It holds the iteration state (current index) internally, eliminating the need for mutable state in `exec_place::impl`.\r\n\r\n- **Removed `exec_place_host`**: The shell class is gone; `exec_place::host()` now returns a plain `exec_place`. This removes static type discrimination in favor of runtime `is_host()` checks where needed.\r\n\r\n- **Removed `exec_place::iterator`**: Replaced range-based iteration with explicit index loops (`for (size_t i = 0; i < place.size(); ++i)`), which is clearer and avoids iterator complexity.\r\n\r\n- **Simplified internal state**: `exec_place_scope` uses an empty `exec_place` (null pimpl) to represent inactive state instead of a separate `bool active_` flag. Removed `std::optional` wrapper from `task.cuh`.\r\n\r\n- **Cleanup**: Removed dead code paths in `place_partition.cuh`, redundant operators in `exec_place_scope`, and applied pass-by-value + `mv()` idiom for sink parameters.\r\n\r\n### Suggested Review Order\r\n\r\n1. **`places.cuh`** — Core changes: `exec_place_scope` definition, removal of `exec_place_host`, simplified `exec_place` API\r\n2. **`place_partition.cuh`** — Updated to use new API, dead code removal, parameter passing cleanup\r\n3. **`launch.cuh`** — Updated iteration pattern (index-based loops)\r\n4. **`task.cuh` / `acquire_release.cuh`** — Simplified `exec_place_scope` usage (no more `std::optional`)\r\n5. **`parallel_for_scope.cuh` / `backend_ctx.cuh`** — Removed `exec_place_host` dependencies",
